,"from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","X_pca = PCA(n_components=2).fit_transform(X_train_resampled)\n","\n","# CONVERT LANELS TO NUMPY ARRAY IF NEEDED\n","# ENSURE LABELS ARE 1-D ARRAY\n","y_labels = np.array(y_train_resampled).ravel()\n","\n","# CREATE CLASS MASKS\n","false_pos_mask = (y_labels == 0)\n","confirmed_mask = (y_labels == 1)\n","\n","# PLOT\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n","plt.scatter(X_pca[false_pos_mask, 0], X_pca[false_pos_mask, 1],\n","            c='red', label='FALSE POSITIVE', alpha=0.6)\n","plt.scatter(X_pca[confirmed_mask, 0], X_pca[confirmed_mask, 1],\n","            c='blue', label='CONFIRMED', alpha=0.6)\n","\n","plt.title(\"PCA Projection of Resampled Training Data\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"PC1\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"PC2\")\n","plt.legend(loc='best')\n","plt.grid(True)\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Z3oMs_2Ta7nI"},"source":["**INTERPRETATION**<br>\n","The second PCA graph, after applying SMOTE, shows a more balanced and distinct separation between the two classes, compared to the first PCA graph. By generating synthethetic points for the minority class, there is a more even distibution of data points and less overlap across both classes. SMOTE improves data separability and the second PCA graph shows more uniform density, which may help to increase model performance by reducing underfitting on the minority class. Therefore, applying SMOTE before PCA helped create a clearer and more balanced representation of the data in the feature space."]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"tARJP8dW5jBn"},"source":["**FEATURE IMPORTANCE**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":536},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":686,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777627427225,"user":{"displayName":"Suzanne Knight","userId":"13236134929098667911"},"user_tz":-480},"id":"cYRgFmjSm3-N","outputId":"b956ebb7-c856-497d-f463-cae859cab78c"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["[0.03330495 0.03946974 0.03438066 0.064278   0.0394753  0.04744901\n"," 0.03486823 0.0564621  0.06466943 0.0462003  0.03031472 0.04313229\n"," 0.0529154  0.05397961 0.04820479 0.05522416 0.0566705  0.05313164\n"," 0.03759627 0.04945442 0.05881848]\n","\n"]},{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["# FEATURE IMPORTANCE\n","# PICKUP HIGHLY CORRELATED (BEST) FEATURES OF CLASSIFICATION DATA\n","\n","# EXTRA TREE CLASSIFIER IS USED TO EXTRACT THE TOP 10 FEATURES FOR THE DATASET\n","# FEATURE IMPORTANCE IS AN INBUILT CLASS THAT COMES WITH TREE-BASED CLASSIFIERS\n","\n","from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","model = ExtraTreesClassifier()\n","model.fit(X,y)\n","print(model.feature_importances_)\n","print()\n","\n","# PLOT THE GRAPH OF FEATURE IMPORTANCE\n","feat_importances = pd.Series(model.feature_importances_, index=X.columns)\n","feat_importances.nlargest(10).sort_values().plot(kind='barh')\n","plt.xlabel('Feature Labels')\n","plt.ylabel('Feature Importances')\n","# plt.title('Comparison of different Feature Importances')\n","plt.show()"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"Mka9dL2OwFu-"},"source":["**INTERPRETATION**<br>\n","\n","The most important features for the model are primarily related to an planet's temperature and physical characteristics (e.g radius).Features such as insolation (log_pl_insol), equilibrium temperature (log_pl_eqt) and effective temperature ratio (ratio_eq_teff) are primary factors in model decision making. <br>\n","Stellar properties such as radius (log_st_rad) and distance (log_st_dist) suggest that while they have some influence, they are not predictive in the outcome in the modelling especially after SMOTE. This could have implications for how the model performs and which features to focus on in further analysis or when improving the model"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"uTaW3r-ImeEP"},"source":["#**4.MODELLING**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"RME-GHUum5GJ"},"source":["**GENERATE MACHINE LEARNING MODELS FOR:**\n","\n","**Support Vector Classifier/Machine: SVC (SVM)**\n","- Well-suited for binary classification tasks where feature engineering is well-optimised\n","\n","**Random Forest (RF)**\n","- Suitable for handling noisy astronomical data, offering strong interpretability, valuable feature importance insights and robustness in finding exoplanets with pronounced transit signals\n","- Used in Autovetter for KEPLER and adapted for TESS\n","\n","**Light Gradient Boosting Machine (LIGHTGBM)**\n","- Excellent for tabular data with mixed feature types\n","- Integrates well with SHAP for interpretability\n","\n","**Neural Networks - Multi-Layer Perceptron(MLP)**\n","- MLPs are flexible and model either nonlinear relationships on tabular data\n","- Captures abstract patterns and feature interactions\n","- Works well with TSFRESH or PCA inputs"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"KC3BdUvEhJdt"},"source":["**DECLARATIONS**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"SkU6rWOzzqe6"},"outputs":[],"source":["# REPORTING METRICS\n","from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix,  ConfusionMatrixDisplay, balanced_accuracy_score, classification_report, cohen_kappa_score, f1_score\n","from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n","\n","from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc\n","from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error,r2_score             # RMSE, Chi-square"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"-059TjE84spf"},"outputs":[],"source":["from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n","from sklearn.svm import SVC\n","from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n","from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline # library to make a pipeline\n","from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"d-tN1xhqLbd6"},"outputs":[],"source":["import pandas as pd\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, RandomizedSearchCV\n","from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n","from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n","from scipy.stats import randint"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"JrhPauE29PWr"},"outputs":[],"source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"KSWz8beIBMqK"},"source":["#**OPTIMISED MODELS - HYPERPARAMETER TUNING**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"w1T1pRKc2fGs"},"outputs":[],"source":["# SKLEARN Library\n","from sklearn import datasets\n","from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_predict               # ANN - Multilayer Perceptron model\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split                # Split method\n","from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV                    # Best parameter value\n","from sklearn.model_selection import RepeatedKFold\n","\n","from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score                 # Cross validation\n","from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score                          # Reporting Metrics\n","\n","from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error                      # RMSE\n","from sklearn.neural_network import MLPClassifier                    # ANN Model\n","from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler                    # Standardises features by removing the mean and scaling to unit variance\n","from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline                               # Pipeline Library"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"F28IEk4MZPmM"},"outputs":[],"source":["# SKLEARN LIBRARY\n","from sklearn import datasets\n","from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_predict               # ANN - Multilayer Perceptron model\n","from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split                # Split method\n","from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV                    # Best parameter value\n","from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score                 # Cross validation\n","from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix # Reporting Metrics\n","from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score                          # Reporting Metrics"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"5zqLGkrZtXhj"},"outputs":[],"source":["from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline # library to make a pipeline\n","from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"8yfV58U8NAzc"},"source":["**4.1 - RANDOM FOREST**"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"SyNfKV5ONrNo"},"source":["**4.1.1 - All Features**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":39,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777627427360,"user":{"displayName":"Suzanne Knight","userId":"13236134929098667911"},"user_tz":-480},"id":"ESwfCfaGNEE1","outputId":"6653d4a1-455b-4155-fa86-36532b9d67c1"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Random Forest - Hypertuning of Parameters\n"]}],"source":["# INSTANTIATE THE RANDOM FOREST MODEL(RF)\n","\n","# FIT PR TO THE SCALED RESAMPLED TRAINING DATASET (X_train_resampled)\n","# PREDICT WITH SCALED TESTING DATASET (X_test_scaled)\n","\n","print('Random Forest - Hypertuning of Parameters')\n","\n","# SET UP THE RANDOM FOREST CLASSIFIER AND HYPERPARAMETER TUNUNG\n","# CREATE A PIPELINE\n","pca=PCA()\n","predictor = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42)\n","\n","# Make pipeline\n","pipe_RF_hyper = make_pipeline(pca, predictor) # Build model with PCA & RFc only"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"Jvdcr-GVNyrw"},"outputs":[],"source":["# FIT MODEL WITH THE TRAINING SUBSET\n","pipe_RF_hyper.fit(X_train_resampled,y_train_resampled) # scaled data (x_sc)\n","\n","# PREDICT USING TEST SUBSET\n","y_RF_hyper_predict_test = pipe_RF_hyper.predict(X_test_scaled)\n","\n","# PREDICT USING TRAIN SUBSET\n","y_RF_hyper_predict_train = pipe_RF_hyper.predict(X_train_resampled)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"executionInfo":{"elapsed":42,"status":"ok","timestamp":1777627428470,"user":{"displayName":"Suzanne Knight","userId":"13236134929098667911"},"user_tz":-480},"id":"v1WDq2D8OJ9v","outputId":"b0f24676-c272-4e1c-d7b6-6d300b4e1e8b"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/plain":["['memory',\n"," 'pca',\n"," 'pca__copy',\n"," 'pca__iterated_power',\n"," 'pca__n_components',\n"," 'pca__n_oversamples',\n"," 'pca__power_iteration_normalizer',\n"," 'pca__random_state',\n"," 'pca__svd_solver',\n"," 'pca__tol',\n"," 'pca__whiten',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__bootstrap',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__ccp_alpha',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__class_weight',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__criterion',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__max_depth',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__max_features',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__max_samples',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__min_impurity_decrease',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__min_weight_fraction_leaf',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__monotonic_cst',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__n_estimators',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__n_jobs',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__oob_score',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__random_state',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__verbose',\n"," 'randomforestclassifier__warm_start',\n"," 'steps',\n"," 'transform_input',\n"," 'verbose']"]},"execution_count":56,"metadata":{},"output_type":"execute_result"}],"source":["# DETERMINE PARAMETERS FOR RANDOMSEARCHRV\n","sorted(pipe_RF_hyper.get_params().keys())"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"id":"WMjYuqNxbydD"},"outputs":[],"source":["# SET UP PARAMETERS FOR RANDOMRIDSEARCHCV\n","\n","import numpy as np    # Operations on arrays\n","\n","# DEFAULT CRITERION IS GINI\n","\n","params_grid = {\n","    'randomforestclassifier__n_estimators': [300, 500, 700, 900], # NO. of trees in the RF\n","    'randomforestclassifier__max_depth':[None, 4, 6, 8],\n","    'randomforestclassifier__max_features': ['sqrt', 'log2', 0.3, 0.5, 1],\n","    'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf':[1, 2, 5, 10, 0.05, 0.1],\n","    'randomforestclassifier__bootstrap': [True, False],\n","    'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split': [2, 5, 10, 13],\n","    'randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes':[None, 10, 20, 50]\n","}\n","\n","scores = [\"f1\", \"balanced_accuracy\"]"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true,"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"SYwK6qANdi26","outputId":"9180cf0d-f07c-4337-f610-7d9fe31c9123"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Fitting 5 folds for each of 100 candidates, totalling 500 fits\n","CPU times: user 40.6 s, sys: 2.32 s, total: 42.9 s\n","Wall time: 31min 57s\n"]},{"data":{"text/html":["<style>#sk-container-id-2 {\n","  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */\n","  --sklearn-color-text: #000;\n","  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;\n","  --sklearn-color-line: gray;\n","  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1: #f6e4d2;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2: #ffe0b3;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3: chocolate;\n","  /* Definition of color scheme for fitted estimators */\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-0: #f0f8ff;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-1: #d4ebff;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-2: #b3dbfd;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-3: cornflowerblue;\n","\n","  /* Specific color for light theme */\n","  --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));\n","  --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, white)));\n","  --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));\n","  --sklearn-color-icon: #696969;\n","\n","  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {\n","    /* Redefinition of color scheme for dark theme */\n","    --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, white)));\n","    --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, #111)));\n","    --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, white)));\n","    --sklearn-color-icon: #878787;\n","  }\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 {\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 pre {\n","  padding: 0;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 input.sk-hidden--visually {\n","  border: 0;\n","  clip: rect(1px 1px 1px 1px);\n","  clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\n","  height: 1px;\n","  margin: -1px;\n","  overflow: hidden;\n","  padding: 0;\n","  position: absolute;\n","  width: 1px;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-dashed-wrapped {\n","  border: 1px dashed var(--sklearn-color-line);\n","  margin: 0 0.4em 0.5em 0.4em;\n","  box-sizing: border-box;\n","  padding-bottom: 0.4em;\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-container {\n","  /* jupyter's `normalize.less` sets `[hidden] { display: none; }`\n","     but bootstrap.min.css set `[hidden] { display: none !important; }`\n","     so we also need the `!important` here to be able to override the\n","     default hidden behavior on the sphinx rendered scikit-learn.org.\n","     See: https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/issues/21755 */\n","  display: inline-block !important;\n","  position: relative;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-text-repr-fallback {\n","  display: none;\n","}\n","\n","div.sk-parallel-item,\n","div.sk-serial,\n","div.sk-item {\n","  /* draw centered vertical line to link estimators */\n","  background-image: linear-gradient(var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background), var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background));\n","  background-size: 2px 100%;\n","  background-repeat: no-repeat;\n","  background-position: center center;\n","}\n","\n","/* Parallel-specific style estimator block */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel-item::after {\n","  content: \"\";\n","  width: 100%;\n","  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background);\n","  flex-grow: 1;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel {\n","  display: flex;\n","  align-items: stretch;\n","  justify-content: center;\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  position: relative;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel-item {\n","  display: flex;\n","  flex-direction: column;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel-item:first-child::after {\n","  align-self: flex-end;\n","  width: 50%;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel-item:last-child::after {\n","  align-self: flex-start;\n","  width: 50%;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-parallel-item:only-child::after {\n","  width: 0;\n","}\n","\n","/* Serial-specific style estimator block */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-serial {\n","  display: flex;\n","  flex-direction: column;\n","  align-items: center;\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  padding-right: 1em;\n","  padding-left: 1em;\n","}\n","\n","\n","/* Toggleable style: style used for estimator/Pipeline/ColumnTransformer box that is\n","clickable and can be expanded/collapsed.\n","- Pipeline and ColumnTransformer use this feature and define the default style\n","- Estimators will overwrite some part of the style using the `sk-estimator` class\n","*/\n","\n","/* Pipeline and ColumnTransformer style (default) */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-toggleable {\n","  /* Default theme specific background. It is overwritten whether we have a\n","  specific estimator or a Pipeline/ColumnTransformer */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","}\n","\n","/* Toggleable label */\n","#sk-container-id-2 label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  cursor: pointer;\n","  display: flex;\n","  width: 100%;\n","  margin-bottom: 0;\n","  padding: 0.5em;\n","  box-sizing: border-box;\n","  text-align: center;\n","  align-items: start;\n","  justify-content: space-between;\n","  gap: 0.5em;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 label.sk-toggleable__label .caption {\n","  font-size: 0.6rem;\n","  font-weight: lighter;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text-muted);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 label.sk-toggleable__label-arrow:before {\n","  /* Arrow on the left of the label */\n","  content: \"▸\";\n","  float: left;\n","  margin-right: 0.25em;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-icon);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 label.sk-toggleable__label-arrow:hover:before {\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","}\n","\n","/* Toggleable content - dropdown */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-toggleable__content {\n","  max-height: 0;\n","  max-width: 0;\n","  overflow: hidden;\n","  text-align: left;\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-toggleable__content.fitted {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-toggleable__content pre {\n","  margin: 0.2em;\n","  border-radius: 0.25em;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-toggleable__content.fitted pre {\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~div.sk-toggleable__content {\n","  /* Expand drop-down */\n","  max-height: 200px;\n","  max-width: 100%;\n","  overflow: auto;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label-arrow:before {\n","  content: \"▾\";\n","}\n","\n","/* Pipeline/ColumnTransformer-specific style */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label.fitted input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","/* Estimator-specific style */\n","\n","/* Colorize estimator box */\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator.fitted input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label label.sk-toggleable__label,\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label label {\n","  /* The background is the default theme color */\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background);\n","}\n","\n","/* On hover, darken the color of the background */\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label:hover label.sk-toggleable__label {\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","/* Label box, darken color on hover, fitted */\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label.fitted:hover label.sk-toggleable__label.fitted {\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","/* Estimator label */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label label {\n","  font-family: monospace;\n","  font-weight: bold;\n","  display: inline-block;\n","  line-height: 1.2em;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-label-container {\n","  text-align: center;\n","}\n","\n","/* Estimator-specific */\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator {\n","  font-family: monospace;\n","  border: 1px dotted var(--sklearn-color-border-box);\n","  border-radius: 0.25em;\n","  box-sizing: border-box;\n","  margin-bottom: 0.5em;\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator.fitted {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-0);\n","}\n","\n","/* on hover */\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator:hover {\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 div.sk-estimator.fitted:hover {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-2);\n","}\n","\n","/* Specification for estimator info (e.g. \"i\" and \"?\") */\n","\n","/* Common style for \"i\" and \"?\" */\n","\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link,\n","a:link.sk-estimator-doc-link,\n","a:visited.sk-estimator-doc-link {\n","  float: right;\n","  font-size: smaller;\n","  line-height: 1em;\n","  font-family: monospace;\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  border-radius: 1em;\n","  height: 1em;\n","  width: 1em;\n","  text-decoration: none !important;\n","  margin-left: 0.5em;\n","  text-align: center;\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  border: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1) 1pt solid;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1);\n","}\n","\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted,\n","a:link.sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted,\n","a:visited.sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  border: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-1) 1pt solid;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-1);\n","}\n","\n","/* On hover */\n","div.sk-estimator:hover .sk-estimator-doc-link:hover,\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link:hover,\n","div.sk-label-container:hover .sk-estimator-doc-link:hover,\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link:hover {\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3);\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  text-decoration: none;\n","}\n","\n","div.sk-estimator.fitted:hover .sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted:hover,\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted:hover,\n","div.sk-label-container:hover .sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted:hover,\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted:hover {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-3);\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  text-decoration: none;\n","}\n","\n","/* Span, style for the box shown on hovering the info icon */\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link span {\n","  display: none;\n","  z-index: 9999;\n","  position: relative;\n","  font-weight: normal;\n","  right: .2ex;\n","  padding: .5ex;\n","  margin: .5ex;\n","  width: min-content;\n","  min-width: 20ex;\n","  max-width: 50ex;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);\n","  box-shadow: 2pt 2pt 4pt #999;\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0);\n","  border: .5pt solid var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3);\n","}\n","\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link.fitted span {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-0);\n","  border: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-3);\n","}\n","\n",".sk-estimator-doc-link:hover span {\n","  display: block;\n","}\n","\n","/* \"?\"-specific style due to the `<a>` HTML tag */\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 a.estimator_doc_link {\n","  float: right;\n","  font-size: 1rem;\n","  line-height: 1em;\n","  font-family: monospace;\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  border-radius: 1rem;\n","  height: 1rem;\n","  width: 1rem;\n","  text-decoration: none;\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1);\n","  border: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1) 1pt solid;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 a.estimator_doc_link.fitted {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  border: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-1) 1pt solid;\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-1);\n","}\n","\n","/* On hover */\n","#sk-container-id-2 a.estimator_doc_link:hover {\n","  /* unfitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3);\n","  color: var(--sklearn-color-background);\n","  text-decoration: none;\n","}\n","\n","#sk-container-id-2 a.estimator_doc_link.fitted:hover {\n","  /* fitted */\n","  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-3);\n","}\n","</style><div id=\"sk-container-id-2\" class=\"sk-top-container\"><div class=\"sk-text-repr-fallback\"><pre>RandomizedSearchCV(cv=5,\n","                   estimator=Pipeline(steps=[(&#x27;pca&#x27;, PCA()),\n","                                             (&#x27;randomforestclassifier&#x27;,\n","                                              RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42))]),\n","                   n_iter=100, n_jobs=-1,\n","                   param_distributions={&#x27;randomforestclassifier__bootstrap&#x27;: [True,\n","                                                                              False],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_depth&#x27;: [None,\n","                                                                              4,\n","                                                                              6,\n","                                                                              8],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_features&#x27;: [&#x27;sqrt&#x27;,\n","                                                                                 &#x27;log2&#x27;,\n","                                                                                 0.3,\n","                                                                                 0.5,\n","                                                                                 1],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes&#x27;: [None,\n","                                                                                   10,\n","                                                                                   20,\n","                                                                                   50],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf&#x27;: [1,\n","                                                                                     2,\n","                                                                                     5,\n","                                                                                     10,\n","                                                                                     0.05,\n","                                                                                     0.1],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split&#x27;: [2,\n","                                                                                      5,\n","                                                                                      10,\n","                                                                                      13],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__n_estimators&#x27;: [300,\n","                                                                                 500,\n","                                                                                 700,\n","                                                                                 900]},\n","                   return_train_score=True, verbose=1)</pre><b>In a Jupyter environment, please rerun this cell to show the HTML representation or trust the notebook. <br />On GitHub, the HTML representation is unable to render, please try loading this page with nbviewer.org.</b></div><div class=\"sk-container\" hidden><div class=\"sk-item sk-dashed-wrapped\"><div class=\"sk-label-container\"><div class=\"sk-label fitted sk-toggleable\"><input class=\"sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually\" id=\"sk-estimator-id-2\" type=\"checkbox\" ><label for=\"sk-estimator-id-2\" class=\"sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow\"><div><div>RandomizedSearchCV</div></div><div><a class=\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.model_selection.RandomizedSearchCV.html\">?<span>Documentation for RandomizedSearchCV</span></a><span class=\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\">i<span>Fitted</span></span></div></label><div class=\"sk-toggleable__content fitted\"><pre>RandomizedSearchCV(cv=5,\n","                   estimator=Pipeline(steps=[(&#x27;pca&#x27;, PCA()),\n","                                             (&#x27;randomforestclassifier&#x27;,\n","                                              RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42))]),\n","                   n_iter=100, n_jobs=-1,\n","                   param_distributions={&#x27;randomforestclassifier__bootstrap&#x27;: [True,\n","                                                                              False],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_depth&#x27;: [None,\n","                                                                              4,\n","                                                                              6,\n","                                                                              8],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_features&#x27;: [&#x27;sqrt&#x27;,\n","                                                                                 &#x27;log2&#x27;,\n","                                                                                 0.3,\n","                                                                                 0.5,\n","                                                                                 1],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes&#x27;: [None,\n","                                                                                   10,\n","                                                                                   20,\n","                                                                                   50],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf&#x27;: [1,\n","                                                                                     2,\n","                                                                                     5,\n","                                                                                     10,\n","                                                                                     0.05,\n","                                                                                     0.1],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split&#x27;: [2,\n","                                                                                      5,\n","                                                                                      10,\n","                                                                                      13],\n","                                        &#x27;randomforestclassifier__n_estimators&#x27;: [300,\n","                                                                                 500,\n","                                                                                 700,\n","                                                                                 900]},\n","                   return_train_score=True, verbose=1)</pre></div> </div></div><div class=\"sk-parallel\"><div class=\"sk-parallel-item\"><div class=\"sk-item\"><div class=\"sk-label-container\"><div class=\"sk-label fitted sk-toggleable\"><input class=\"sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually\" id=\"sk-estimator-id-3\" type=\"checkbox\" ><label for=\"sk-estimator-id-3\" class=\"sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow\"><div><div>best_estimator_: Pipeline</div></div></label><div class=\"sk-toggleable__content fitted\"><pre>Pipeline(steps=[(&#x27;pca&#x27;, PCA()),\n","                (&#x27;randomforestclassifier&#x27;,\n","                 RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=False, max_features=0.3,\n","                                        min_samples_leaf=2, n_estimators=700,\n","                                        random_state=42))])</pre></div> </div></div><div class=\"sk-serial\"><div class=\"sk-item\"><div class=\"sk-serial\"><div class=\"sk-item\"><div class=\"sk-estimator fitted sk-toggleable\"><input class=\"sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually\" id=\"sk-estimator-id-4\" type=\"checkbox\" ><label for=\"sk-estimator-id-4\" class=\"sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow\"><div><div>PCA</div></div><div><a class=\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.decomposition.PCA.html\">?<span>Documentation for PCA</span></a></div></label><div class=\"sk-toggleable__content fitted\"><pre>PCA()</pre></div> </div></div><div class=\"sk-item\"><div class=\"sk-estimator fitted sk-toggleable\"><input class=\"sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually\" id=\"sk-estimator-id-5\" type=\"checkbox\" ><label for=\"sk-estimator-id-5\" class=\"sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow\"><div><div>RandomForestClassifier</div></div><div><a class=\"sk-estimator-doc-link fitted\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestClassifier.html\">?<span>Documentation for RandomForestClassifier</span></a></div></label><div class=\"sk-toggleable__content fitted\"><pre>RandomForestClassifier(bootstrap=False, max_features=0.3, min_samples_leaf=2,\n","                       n_estimators=700, random_state=42)</pre></div> </div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>"],"text/plain":["RandomizedSearchCV(cv=5,\n","                   estimator=Pipeline(steps=[('pca', PCA()),\n","                                             ('randomforestclassifier',\n","                                              RandomForestClassifier(random_state=42))]),\n","                   n_iter=100, n_jobs=-1,\n","                   param_distributions={'randomforestclassifier__bootstrap': [True,\n","                                                                              False],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__max_depth': [None,\n","                                                                              4,\n","                                                                              6,\n","                                                                              8],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__max_features': ['sqrt',\n","                                                                                 'log2',\n","                                                                                 0.3,\n","                                                                                 0.5,\n","                                                                                 1],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes': [None,\n","                                                                                   10,\n","                                                                                   20,\n","                                                                                   50],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf': [1,\n","                                                                                     2,\n","                                                                                     5,\n","                                                                                     10,\n","                                                                                     0.05,\n","                                                                                     0.1],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split': [2,\n","                                                                                      5,\n","                                                                                      10,\n","                                                                                      13],\n","                                        'randomforestclassifier__n_estimators': [300,\n","                                                                                 500,\n","                                                                                 700,\n","                                                                                 900]},\n","                   return_train_score=True, verbose=1)"]},"execution_count":58,"metadata":{},"output_type":"execute_result"}],"source":["# SEARCH FOR OPTIMAL MODEL FROM PARAM GRID\n","\n","grid_RF_opt = RandomizedSearchCV(\n","    estimator=pipe_RF_hyper,\n","    param_distributions=params_grid,\n","    n_iter=100,\n","    cv=5,\n","    verbose=1,\n","    # random_state=42,\n","    n_jobs=-1,\n","    return_train_score=True\n",")\n","\n","\n","# CHECKING HOW MUCH TIME TAKEN TO FIND OPTIMUM VALUE\n","%time grid_RF_opt.fit(X_train_resampled,y_train_resampled) # scaled data (x_sc)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"8wbgQQ1OqNFv","outputId":"5de81b32-5a33-48e0-a416-bedc434b3400"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Best parameters found:  {'randomforestclassifier__n_estimators': 700, 'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_split': 2, 'randomforestclassifier__min_samples_leaf': 2, 'randomforestclassifier__max_leaf_nodes': None, 'randomforestclassifier__max_features': 0.3, 'randomforestclassifier__max_depth': None, 'randomforestclassifier__bootstrap': False}\n","Best accuracy score:  0.8564590222539994\n"]}],"source":["# PRINT THE BEST PARAMETERS AND THE BEST SCORE\n","print(\"Best parameters found: \", grid_RF_opt.best_params_)\n","print(\"Best accuracy score: \", grid_RF_opt.best_score_)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"kfepQ1ubqdEz"},"source":["**INTERPRETATION**\n","\n","- **n_estimators = 500**- The dataset has enough complexity or noise that the model stabilises only with a decent ensemble of trees<br>\n","- **min_samples_split = 2 & min_samples_leaf = 2** - optimiser determined that limited splitting did not improve generalisation. Data benefits from fine-grained splits early in the tree. Preventing 1-sample leaves reduces overfitting on the noisy points. The data is fairly clean or well-separated aafter processing/resampling<br>\n","- **max_depth=None** - dataset has complex non-linear structure that benefits from deeper fully grown trees<br>\n","- **max_leaf_nodes=None** - dataset benefits from flexible trees rather than eexplicit pruning<br>\n","- **max_features = 0.3** - the model samples only third of the available features at each split. There is strong feature redundancy giving better splits.<br>\n","- **bootstrap = false** - full dataset is used for every tree, stabilising splits and reduces variance per tree, giving more consistent learning<br><br>\n","High randomness and diversity produces high ensemble diversity and more stable model generalisation<br>\n","A best accuracy (~0.856) is a strong score, especially for astrophysical classification like TESS candidates where noise is significant, classes overlap and resampled datasets can distort decision boundaries<br>\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"QssziIywrcb5","outputId":"8fd41487-cd53-43bb-9e54-1a7d066da282"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["(1672, 21)\n","Accuracy score 0.859\n"]}],"source":["# ASSIGN BEST PARAMETERS AND FIT MODEL\n","# CREATE RF MODEL WITH OPTIMAL PARAMETERS\n","\n","from sklearn import metrics\n","from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score\n","\n","# ASSIGN THE BEST PARAMETERS AND FIT THE MODEL\n","model_RF_opt = grid_RF_opt.best_estimator_\n","\n","print(X_train_resampled.shape)\n","\n","# FIT THE MODEL\n","model_RF_opt.fit(X_train_resampled, y_train_resampled) # scaled data (x_sc)\n","\n","# PREDICTING TEST DATASET RESULT UNDER MODEL\n","y_predict_RF_opt = model_RF_opt.predict(X_test_scaled) # scaled data (x_sc)\n","\n","# MEASURE THE PERFORMANCE\n","print('Accuracy score %.3f' %metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt)) # Scaled data (x_sc)\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"9jclz26gsoAF","outputId":"68fae486-dca0-4bf3-cb9c-cae90e60a1d9"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["{'0': {'precision': 0.8738317757009346, 'recall': 0.8577981651376146, 'f1-score': 0.8657407407407407, 'support': 218.0}, '1': {'precision': 0.8426395939086294, 'recall': 0.8601036269430051, 'f1-score': 0.8512820512820513, 'support': 193.0}, 'accuracy': 0.8588807785888077, 'macro avg': {'precision': 0.8582356848047821, 'recall': 0.8589508960403098, 'f1-score': 0.8585113960113959, 'support': 411.0}, 'weighted avg': {'precision': 0.8591843521342317, 'recall': 0.8588807785888077, 'f1-score': 0.8589511371749814, 'support': 411.0}}\n"]}],"source":["# GENERATE CLASSIFIICATION REPORT\n","\n","report = classification_report(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt, output_dict=True)\n","print(report)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"fPT-Cx4Is3BY","outputId":"e0c0a4ac-acd2-41ef-a4c1-59823f2713b7"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["F1 Score: 0.8589511371749814\n","Kappa Score: 0.7170496629000095\n","Accuracy Score: 0.8589508960403098\n","Confusion Matrix:\n","[[187  31]\n"," [ 27 166]]\n","{'0': {'precision': 0.8738317757009346, 'recall': 0.8577981651376146, 'f1-score': 0.8657407407407407, 'support': 218.0}, '1': {'precision': 0.8426395939086294, 'recall': 0.8601036269430051, 'f1-score': 0.8512820512820513, 'support': 193.0}, 'accuracy': 0.8588807785888077, 'macro avg': {'precision': 0.8582356848047821, 'recall': 0.8589508960403098, 'f1-score': 0.8585113960113959, 'support': 411.0}, 'weighted avg': {'precision': 0.8591843521342317, 'recall': 0.8588807785888077, 'f1-score': 0.8589511371749814, 'support': 411.0}}\n"]}],"source":["# EVALUATE THE MODEL - CONFUSION MATRIX\n","conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt)\n","f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt, average='weighted')\n","report = classification_report(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt, output_dict=True)\n","accuracy = balanced_accuracy_score(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt)\n","kappa = cohen_kappa_score(y_test, y_predict_RF_opt)\n","\n","print(f\"F1 Score: {f1}\")\n","print(f\"Kappa Score: {kappa}\")\n","print(f\"Accuracy Score: {accuracy}\")\n","print(f\"Confusion Matrix:\\n{conf_matrix}\")\n","print(report)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"dy6eWB1itiyW","outputId":"bf945efa-9ee8-4fcb-af5e-e34cce4ec540"},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["                precision    recall  f1-score     support\n","FALSE POSITIVE   0.873832  0.857798  0.865741  218.000000\n","CONFIRMED        0.842640  0.860104  0.851282  193.000000\n","accuracy         0.858881  0.858881  0.858881    0.858881\n","macro avg        0.858236  0.858951  0.858511  411.000000\n","weighted avg     0.859184  0.858881  0.858951  411.000000 \n","\n"]}],"source":["# REPORTING METRICS\n","# EVALUATE THE MODEL\n","\n","# CONVERT THE REPORT TO A DATAFRAME\n","df_report = pd.DataFrame(report).transpose()\n","\n","# RENAME THE INDEX LABELS\n","df_report.rename(index={'0': 'FALSE POSITIVE', '1': 'CONFIRMED'}, inplace=True)\n","\n","# DISPLAY THE DATAFRAME\n","print(df_report, '\\n')"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"2j_KDeK-d7OA"},"source":["**SAVE MODEL GRID**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"Xh0AnMAAd9pY","outputId":"147a6d05-3da8-4e69-c02b-443246fe9abf"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/plain":["['/content/drive/MyDrive/grid_RF_opt_PORT.joblib']"]},"execution_count":64,"metadata":{},"output_type":"execute_result"}],"source":["import joblib\n","\n","# SAVE MODEL VALUES\n","joblib.dump(grid_RF_opt, ('/content/drive/MyDrive/grid_RF_opt_PORT.joblib'))"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"colab":{"background_save":true},"id":"NXutEso8tuiS","outputId":"d5a9e0cd-f4d2-44a2-e8e4-3ddbb7c5f0dc"},"outputs":[{"data":{"text/html":["<style type=\"text/css\">\n","#T_80c21 caption {\n","  caption-side: top;\n","  font-size: 16px;\n","  font-weight: bold;\n","}\n","#T_80c21_row0_col0, #T_80c21_row0_col2, #T_80c21_row1_col1, #T_80c21_row3_col3, #T_80c21_row4_col3 {\n","  background-color: #081d58;\n","  color: #f1f1f1;\n","  text-align: center;\n","}\n","#T_80c21_row0_col1, #T_80c21_row1_col0, #T_80c21_row1_col2, #T_80c21_row2_col3 {\n","  background-color: #ffffd9;\n","  color: #000000;\n","  text-align: center;\n","}\n","#T_80c21_row0_col3, #T_80c21_row4_col0, #T_80c21_row4_col2 {\n","  background-color: #39adc3;\n","  color: #f1f1f1;\n","  text-align: center;\n","}\n","#T_80c21_row1_col3 {\n","  background-color: #52bcc2;\n","  color: #000000;\n","  text-align: center;\